<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747410>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Onthophagus osculatii. (a, b) Dorsal habitus of male (neotype) and female (scale bar: 1 mm). (g, h) Lateral and dorsal view of the parameres (scale bar: 0.05 mm). (k, l) Lamella copulatrix and accessory lamellae; arrow indicating the basolateral carina of the inferior left lobe of O. osculatii. (m) Female genitalia (scale bar: 0.02 mm); arrow indicating the slight medial excavation of the ventral sclerotization of O. osculatii. Onthophagus chacoensis sp. nov. (c, d) Dorsal habitus of male (holotype) and female. (e) Metasternal punctuation (scale bar: 1 mm). (f) Detail of the pronotal punctuation. (i, j) Lateral and dorsal view of the parameres (scale bar: 0.05 mm). (n, o) Lamella copulatrix and accessory lamellae; arrow indicating the deep excavation of the external margin of the left lobe of O. chacoensis. (p) Female genitalia (scale bar: 0.02 mm)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747410/files/figure.png" .

